organic_results.title: Images of the practitioner and strategies of educational change
organic_results.snippet: Three strategies of planned educational change are derived from current discussions about educational innovation. Each strategy is based on a particular image of the practitioner: as a Rational Man, as a Cooperator, and as a Powerless Functionary. The strategies are described in terms of their locus of change, channel of influence and change-agent; and their efficiency is assessed in terms of effort, coverage and yield.
